CREATE TABLE `Project_Employee` (

CREATE TABLE `Project` (
	`ProjectID` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL, 
	`Name` VARCHAR(255), 
	`Location` VARCHAR(255), 
	`Status` VARCHAR(255), 
	`StartDate` DATE, 
	`EndDate` DATE, 
	`Asset` VARCHAR(255), 
	PRIMARY KEY (`ProjectID`)
)COLLATE utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4

sql_template: SELECT Employee.Name, Project.Name, Company.Name FROM Employee JOIN Project_Employee ON Employee.EmployeeID = Project_Employee.EmployeeID JOIN Project ON Project.ProjectID = Project_Employee.ProjectID JOIN Company_Project ON Project.ProjectID = Company_Project.ProjectID JOIN Company ON Company.CompanyID = Company_Project.CompanyID WHERE Employee.Name = [Employee.Name] AND Project.Name = [Project.Name] AND  Company.Name = [Company.Name];
